Sap inoculation of the 11 [$WMV#Virus*] isolates onto a range of 13 plant species revealed some differences compared to the [$WMV#Virus*] isolates collected from other countries.
Our results showed that, overall, there were no obvious correlations of host responses to inoculation with [$WMV#Virus*] isolates from different geographical origins.
However, isolate JS-1 caused mild mosaic on[$ Cucurbita#Plant*] moschata, whereas the remaining 10 isolates were asymptomatic on this plant species.
Moreover, in [$Datura stramonium#Plant*], isolate TYG-1 induced mosaic, whereas the remaining 10 isolates did not infect this species.
