All isolates did not induce any symptoms on [$Cucumis sativus#Plant*], but the virus could be detected [$using RT-PCR#Method*].
Additionally, all isolates infected systemically [$Nicotiana tabacum#Plant*] plants, causing mild mosaics.
[$Chenopodium amaranticolor#Plant*] and [$Chenopodium quinoa#Plant*] reacted to all isolates by chlorotic local lesions in the inoculated leaves, and the virus was detected in the inoculated leaves [$using RT-PCR#Method*].
